Photo by @amivitale. Mealtime for an elephant calf at Reteti Elephant Sanctuary (@r.e.s.c.u.e) in Northern Kenya. Reteti is currently home to 12 elephant calves rescued from the surrounding Mathews Range, where Kenya's second-largest elephant population roams. The calves are being rehabilitated and protected until they can be reunited with their wild herds. Baby elephants depend on their mothers' milk for the first two years of their lives and can drink nearly 20 pints a day when they are young. 
